  "texts": [
    "However, GNNs also have limitations in the context of drug synergy prediction and in general.",
    "GNNs can be computationally intensive, and their complex architecture often demands a substantial amount of data for effective training.",
    "On the other hand, the space of possible drug combinations is vast, and only a small fraction of potential drug pairs has been experimentally tested.",
    "This sparsity in the synergy space can make it difficult for GNNs to make accurate predictions, especially for untested combinations.",
    "With limited data and complex models, there is a high risk of overfitting, where the model learns to perform well on the training data but fails to generalize to new drug combinations."
  ],
